            CanSAS 1-D Data Format, v1.0
        </para>
        <note><para>
            Provide a note here describing CanSAS and the initiative to establish
            a standard file format.
        </para></note>
        <para>
            "CanSAS" stands for "Collective Action for Nomadic Small-Angle Scatterers.
        </para>
        <para>
            This work is the initiative of the CanSAS 1D Data Formats Working Group, 
            established at the canSAS-V workshop, NIST, Gaithersburg, Maryland, 
            USA from October 29th to 31st 2007.  It derives many of its foundations
            from previous works such as the SASXML format, a joint collaboration
            between ISIS and ILL.
        </para>
        <para>
            The home page of the CanSAS 1D Data Formats Working Group
            <link 
                xlink:href="http://www.smallangles.net/wgwiki/index.php/1D_Data_Formats_Working_Group"
                >http://www.smallangles.net/wgwiki/index.php/1D_Data_Formats_Working_Group</link>
            describes the members, timelines, and current status.
            There is a discussion page for some matters that preceded this revision.
            <link 
                xlink:href="http://www.smallangles.net/wgwiki/index.php/Talk:1D_Data_Formats_Working_Group"
                >http://www.smallangles.net/wgwiki/index.php/Talk:1D_Data_Formats_Working_Group</link>        </para>
